This paper deals with frequent itemsets mining, which is a common task in data mining and falls under the scope of databases (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also presents a statistical test for identifying real frequent itemsets, which involves concepts from statistical learning theory (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of multiple hypothesis testing corrections, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
